Hello all,

Saathi invites applications for the post of UG student mentor for the
academic year 201617.

About Saathi:

The role of Mitr has been to reduced to the reactive position for effective
functioning. The proactive front of the organisation has now offshoot into
a new team called Saathi.

Saathi  endeavors to identify challenges faced by the student community,
understand them, create awareness and to help transform the understanding
into positive action. Our objective includes to achieve overall wellbeing
of the entire student community by equipping and enhancing their
selfmentoring abilities and skills needed to succeed on campus and in life.

Eligibility criteria:

   

   CGPA of 7 and above
   

   BTech/DD/ M.A student of any year (Yes, current first years can apply
   too!)

Responsibilities:

   

   Care for the general wellbeing of the student community on campus
   

   Acting as a guide to freshies by helping them out and overcome any kind
   of hurdles during their first year (emotional support exempted)
   

   Being able to notice or identify student problems/students with problems
   and take sufficient proactive measures and/or novel initiatives to address
   the same.
   

   Be available during Orientation and other situations of emergency (not
   the cases of  isolation, depression, attempt to suicide etc which need
   timely escalation they have to be escalated to Mitr and Medall as they
   will be more equipped to help those in need)

Incentives:

   

   An opportunity to give back to the institute and make a difference
   

   A letter of appreciation for best two mentors of the hostel signed by
   Dean (students)
   

   Tshirts and more ..


Interested students are requested to fill the application
 by  11.59pm, 24th June, 2016

For any queries, feel free to contact:


